
=  monitors and reports on examples of shareable civic technology that can improve public services [http://www.civicexchange.eu/about]

URL = http://www.civicexchange.eu/

Formerly [[Europe Commons]]; Civic Exchange is run by Nesta in collaboration with our Code for Europe partners.


=Description=

"The site is for anyone interested in using technology to solve civic problems, from service providers looking for ideas to those who have apps and services they would like to share. We fully support open innovation – such as releasing software as open source, open APIs or using and/or providing open data – but also believe it’s important to showcase proprietary software if it has created a positive impact on local services."
(http://www.civicexchange.eu/about)


